<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-08-05T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-08-05T07:00:00-05:00" n="245" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d245">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">320/8–553: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State at
                                    Seoul</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Seoul</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-08-05T21:00:00+09:00">August 5,
                                    1953—9 p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Dulte 11. Re Tedul 6. Agree you inform <persName corresp="#p_WWPWWKNB1">Prince Wan</persName> soonest. You should offer Thailand <gloss target="#t_ECOSOC1">ECOSOC</gloss> or Trusteeship Council. Do not
                            approve giving our support to Thailand for Security Council. <persName corresp="#p_LODGEHCJ1">Lodge</persName> and I believe current threat
                            to Thai position makes her risky candidate for Security Council. Believe
                            you should move ahead with the Turk candidacy for the Greek seat on
                                <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_DULLESJF1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                                </persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>